comment: Millsap (ATL) cleanly knocks the ball away from Jones (HOU).
Horford (ATL) contests the hook shot by Jones (HOU), making "high-five" contact with his hand after the release of the shot, which is legal.
Teague (ATL) loses control of the ball as he tries to avoid Beverley (HOU) in transition.
Horford (ATL) contests the jump shot by Ariza (HOU), making "high-five" contact with his hand after the release of the shot, which is legal, and he gives Ariza room to land .
Carroll (ATL) grabs Jones (HOU) preventing him from attempting the layup.
Motiejunas (HOU) jumps vertically while in the restricted area to contest the dunk attempt by Millsap (ATL).

Referees communicated with the Replay Center to determine if the shot clock should be reset after Millsap's (ATL) FGA. The referees' decision that the ball did not hit the rim was upheld. Clocks adjusted accordingly.

Correct call on the foul. Question of timing for common foul (after release) vs away-from-play (before). Players may engage prior to an inbound pass, but a foul occurs when FOM is restricted. Carroll (ATL) is creating space when the ball is OOB. Then Ariza (HOU) affects his FOM as the pass is released. Correct call. However, we have reinforced the need to use replay when plays are close.
Beverley (HOU) grabs the arm of Millsap (ATL), preventing him from catching the entry pass into the post.
Brewer (HOU) commits a take foul on Teague (ATL).
